    "lost-taste": {
      "type": "lost-taste",
      "settings": {
        "section_heading": "Bringing Back the Lost Taste",
        "section_content": "Somewhere along the way, fruit lost its taste, and part of its vitality. Picked too early, stored too long, and grown for convenience instead of flavor. We started Jurassic Fruit to uncover nature’s hidden treasures across the world. Fruits with real character, full of life and yes, sometimes looking like they’ve been around since the dinosaurs...",
        "slide1_image": "shopify://shop_images/Geo-Clement-Small.png",
        "slide1_heading": "It started with a taste we couldn’t forget",
        "slide1_content": "It all started with two childhood friends, raised a little differently: on fruit, curiosity, and maybe a little too much Jurassic Park.<br><br>\nWhile most kids were obsessed with candy, we were obsessed with durian. Seriously.\n<br><br>\nYears later, that same sense of wonder turned into frustration. The fruits we found on supermarket shelves tasted nothing like the ones we grew up with: flavorless, rushed, disconnected from the earth.",
        "slide2_background": "shopify://shop_images/counter-bg.jpg",
        "slide2_image": "shopify://shop_images/Durian-Farm-Scarlett-Vietnam-May2023-2897-JurassicFruit.jpg",
        "slide2_content": "In 2016, we decided to change that. Soon joined by a third partner, we launched Jurassic Fruit with a simple mission: to bring real flavor back to the table.<br><br>\nExotic and wildly delicious fruits, grown with care, picked at peak ripeness, and often impossible to find anywhere else in Europe.<br><br>\nWhat began as a shared childhood dream is now a growing tribe, of farmers, adventurers, and flavor lovers, all rediscovering what fruits were always meant to be."
      }
    },
